,Recommended,253940,3604723,"Posted: 28 September, 2013",all,Littlepip™,"Septerra Core is a fantastic Eastern RPG-style adventure (ala Final Fantasy) set in one of the most unique worlds ever; Septerra. It's a planet consisting of layers, which encircle one another as well as the Core, and descending and ascending between these planetary continents forms the basis of the overworld exploration.As an older game, there's very limited options to configure, but this surprisingly doesn't hinder it that much as it's mouse-driven with pre-rendered backgrounds. There's a number of glitches you'll likely encounter, so I'd make sure to check the Internet for solutions to common problems encountered with modern versions of Windows. If you can get over these hitches, you'll find an engaging setting with likeable characters and turn-based combat reminiscent of the SNES / Playstation era.I truly hope that the sales of this title encourage them to update it, or maybe, one can hope, remake it in HD, because it's something that everyone who's a fan of RPGs can enjoy, and that more people should experience."
