76561198061797556,Recommended,253940,9691140,"Posted: 31 March, 2014",all,Mr. Bands,"If you loved games like Legend Of Dragoon, Final fantasy, Chrono Trigger, and any other awesome JRPG then you're sure to love septerra core!"
,Recommended,253940,7319091,"Posted: 5 October, 2013",all,GRRRR,"I remember playing this off a PS1 demo disc back in the day and being somewhat intrigued but not impressed since FF7 was still a thing. Nowadays i cant stomach jrpg style round based combat anymore but to my surprise sunk quite some hours into this already because it puts a good spin on the formula.Theres the typical ATB system but its kinda like charging up instead of waiting for the bar to fully fill to being able to do something. Theres 3 levels - If you just wanna pop a potion or do a quick weak attack you can do that at the first level which is full usually in like 3 seconds. Second level delivers more oomph and third level delivers major oomph (double and triple with damage bonus else what would be the point of waiting) and all levels also have special attacks available. At the start when theres not many options its still unfortunately a snorefest but when you get more dudes with differing attack strength and charge speed it gets interesting, moreso since its all realtime (it stops when you click your dudes to select actions tho).Also no random battles, you can see all enemies on the map.Graphic style and character design is interesting/weird, like FF7 and Baldurs Gate mashed together - i guess western rpgs needed more anime hair. Simple and sensible story by comparision. Some tedium like multiple treks thru the same frikking cave but thats the nature of the beast prolly.Surpassed my expectations by a long shot."
