76561198097988719,Recommended,253940,21844908,"Posted: 14 March, 2016",all,OCracks,"Ok so...I never played this game way back when, so I won't say that I played this out of nostalgia. I never played any of those angled top down point and click games like Diablo, so I won't say I'm familiar with those kind of games. But I love an RPG, especially if it promises to be a great experience!I got this game for $0.64, a good price, especially if you use money you earned by selling cards on the Steam Community Market.The games started out fine, but then I realized that it was missing cutscenes.Don't worry, I fixed it within the hour using these steps: just follow the ""How to get Septerra Core working fully guide"" in the Steam Community, then uninstall the current quicktime program, install the version of quicktime in the Septerra steam folder, set the compatitbility mode of the program to Windows XP (SP2), and open up QuickTime, go to Preferences > QuickTime Preferences > Advanced > Uncheck the three DirectX check boxes. Done!So, back to the actual gameThe graphics look outdated, but for being a game of its time, I can overlook it. The plot is engaging, I like the setting, and the combat, while slow, might speed up later in the game. If you can get this game for a good price and get it to work, I would totally recommend this!"
