,Recommended,253940,18145524,"Posted: 22 September, 2015",all,Razonix,"The first time I've met this game was when I went to my friend's home and he was playing it. He said that it was really fun and since he's such a big fan of RPGs, I've taken his word for granted. A few months later I've seen it for sale and decided to give it a try. Well, to be quite honest I wasn't so thrilled with it so I've put it aside and didn't touched it again, that until Steam reminded me of its existence. After all those years I just felt like giving it another shot (especially because the price was alright). To be quite honest, it wasn't such a bad experience... Well, actually it doesn't offer much replay value, because there're some really tedious mazes and a whole lot of grinding, so I just feel like taking an instant nap when I think of it. Besides that, if you don't have a FAQ to provide you some support during your run, things can get even more annoying. The story isn't bad, the characters are somewhat generic, the gameplay is ok, the soundtrack is fine too, but nothing memorable anyway. I won't say anything about the graphics because after all, we're talking about an outdated game. Although I'm recommending it here, my thoughts about Septerra Core are kinda mixed, so I'd only advise hardcore JRPG fans to try it and even so they might simply feel disappointed."
