76561198115845352,Recommended,253940,18461507,"Posted: 13 October, 2015",all,Swiss,"So I didn't grow up with this game, but overall still fun. Satisfied with the purchase even without the nostalgia.Story 4 of 5- Good plot, a cool world and intersting enough to make me binge play although it could have had a better flow.  At times it almost rushes the plot, at others you are watching paint dry.  Similar feel of other nostalgic games, Final Fantasy, Chrono trigger, ect.Battles 3.5 of 5- Unique style, but limited customization probably due to the age of the game.  Only thing I didn't like was that battles took so freakishingly long to do, character animations included it made battles way too long.Characters 4 of 5- Good job with what they had to work with back then.  You definately find your favorites pretty quick.As far as all these comments mentioning glitches? I haven't run into a single one, back in the day these games took something called 'patience'  for things to load up and looks like people are taking them as glitches.  Sometimes your character won't walk to where you click it... probably because where you clicked isn't ""movable space to walk on"".  This is normal and it might make your character walk in the opposite direction.  Not a glitch.Also, if you are expecting the game to spoonfeed what to do next, forget it.  This is when games took thought, no fight tutorial, and no hints on what to do next.  It's all on brains and sheer stubborness to beat the game.Overall: would buy again"
