,Recommended,253940,21865738,"Posted: 16 March, 2016",all,dj_moyer,"Outdated and GLITCHY but fun.  Worth working through the glitches and bugs.  Just don't pay more than $5 or else you will feel like an idiot.Really the only good thing about this game is the story, which will keep you wondering what really is going on for a good while.  If you are looking for an old RPG that is nothing like the Final Fantasy series but has a unique charm, then get this one.  Just be aware that there are a few tricks you will need to set it up to run properly before you can play.  And during the game you will need a bit of patience to iron out or avoid a couple of nasty glitches.The music is terrible and choppy, and often just decides to quit altogether.  The voice recordings are not particularly good, either.  Conversation with NPCs and party members is done by static head images with dialogue windows.  Battle is turn-based with a timer for each player; a level 2 action means a longer wait than a level 1 action.  Sometimes you will have to grind for XP and money before you can make any significant progress.  And you will never be sure where you are supposed to go next, so maybe have a good walthrough guide handy while you play."
