,Recommended,253940,19985733,"Posted: 26 December, 2015",all,Misty,"How should I begin to review this gem?Septerra Core is an old game with outdated graphics. I love the game because of its storyline. It is about a world with seven rotating shells. In the middle of all these shells is the Core, which contains a hidden power. Each shell resides different types of people. The furthest shell from the Core belongs to the Chosen Ones. One of the Chosen General has decided to harness the power of the Core for his own. You are Maya. Together with your companions, you will try to stop the General and bring balance to all seven shells.Battle is somewhat turn-based with a twist. You can activate which power level for your characters. Maya can choose any two companions before entering a battle, somewhat similar to other Japanese-type games. The game duration is surprisingly quite long for an old game.100% satisfaction."
